comments: Abolished 30.9.1896 and added to the parish of Central Bristol.

Created 1.4.1898 from the parishes of North Bristol, South Bristol, 
    St. George, Central Bristol and Stapleton. Abolished 1.4.1974 to become an 
    unparished area. See also Table 2, notes (a) to (x).
Abolished 30.9.1896 and added to the parish of Central Bristol.

    St. James In, St. Michael, St. Mary Redcliff, Temple, St. Philip & St. Jacob 
    In, St. Stephen, Castle Precincts, St. Nicholas, St. Peter, St. Thomas, St. 
    John The Baptist, All Saints, Christchurch, St. Ewen, St. Mary-le-Port and 
    St. Leonard. Abolished 1.4.1898 and added to the parish of Bristol.
